<div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />How comes so many NES games were ported to MSX ?<br /></div><br />I guess games were ported to C64, MSX, etc. because even ColecoVision/SG-1000 style 1bpp sprites were better sprites than other home computers available in Japan and other MSX markets had at the time. Not everybody who could afford an 8-bit home computer could also afford a separate game console, and some MSX markets had much higher import duties for dedicated game consoles than for home computers.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Nov 26, 2013 8:39 am</p><hr />
