<author><name><![CDATA[Shiru]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-11-26T01:45:56-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-11-26T01:45:56-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10720&amp;p=121527#p121527</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10720&amp;p=121527#p121527"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Dracula in the MSX version of &quot;Castlevania&quot;]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10720&amp;p=121527#p121527"><![CDATA[
MSX1 has 1bpp 16x16 sprites, 4 per scanline. MSX2 has 1bpp 'multicolored' 16x16 sprites, 8 per scanline. Multicolored means each horizontal pixel line of a sprite can have its own color. To get more colors you have to overlap sprites.<br /><br />MSX2 also has entirely different blitter-like rendering system which allows to have as much sprites as one wants, in trade of speed.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Tue Nov 26, 2013 1:45 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
